---
layout: null
sitemap: false
---
{%- comment -%}
  Custom sitemap. Overrides the jekyll-sitemap plugin's default template.

  Why replace the plugin output:
  jekyll-sitemap's default template iterates site.static_files with no
  extension filter and emits a <url> entry for every static asset — for
  this repo that's ~60 PNGs, plus CSS, JS, robots.txt, and every naked
  article.md include fragment. Google Search Console has been rejecting
  the resulting file. Constraining the sitemap to actual content pages
  (index, whoami, and every post) produces valid, minimal XML that
  Search Console accepts.

  Why the plugin doesn't fight us:
  jekyll-sitemap skips its own generator when a file named `sitemap.xml`
  already exists in the source tree, so this file wins by being here.
  The front matter `sitemap: false` also prevents the file from listing
  itself if the plugin's page filter is ever run over it.

  Content model:
  Posts are `.md` files under /posts/*/index.md with `layout: post`, the
  same filter the home page uses to list entries. We add /, /whoami/,
  and every such post. `<lastmod>` prefers `last_modified_at` when set
  and falls back to `date`.

  Backup-file defence:
  Files like `posts/4g/index.md.before-combined-site-update-…` carry
  `layout: post` in their front matter and, since Jekyll processes any
  file with front matter regardless of extension, get treated as
  duplicate posts. `_config.yml` now excludes `**/*.before-*` and
  friends so those files never reach `_site`, but as belt-and-braces
  we also filter their URLs out of the sitemap by rejecting anything
  whose URL contains `.before-`, `.bak`, or `.orig`. A single leftover
  is enough for Search Console to refuse the whole file.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign posts_raw = site.pages
      | where: "layout", "post"
      | sort: "date"
      | reverse
-%}
{%- assign posts = "" | split: "" -%}
{%- for post in posts_raw -%}
  {%- assign url = post.url -%}
  {%- unless url contains ".before-" or url contains ".bak" or url contains ".orig" -%}
    {%- assign posts = posts | push: post -%}
  {%- endunless -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- assign latest_post = posts | first -%}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
  <url>
    <loc>{{ '/' | absolute_url | xml_escape }}</loc>
    {%- if latest_post %}
    <lastmod>{{ latest_post.last_modified_at | default: latest_post.date | date_to_xmlschema }}</lastmod>
    {%- else %}
    <lastmod>{{ site.time | date_to_xmlschema }}</lastmod>
    {%- endif %}
    <changefreq>weekly</changefreq>
    <priority>1.0</priority>
  </url>
  <url>
    <loc>{{ '/whoami/' | absolute_url | xml_escape }}</loc>
    <lastmod>{{ site.time | date_to_xmlschema }}</lastmod>
    <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
    <priority>0.6</priority>
  </url>
  {%- for post in posts %}
  <url>
    <loc>{{ post.url | replace: '/index.html', '/' | absolute_url | xml_escape }}</loc>
    <lastmod>{{ post.last_modified_at | default: post.date | date_to_xmlschema }}</lastmod>
    <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
    <priority>0.8</priority>
  </url>
  {%- endfor %}
</urlset>
